  "texts": [
    "We also show how to make use of different target captions to enhance our fine-tuning paradigm in Sec.",
    "3.3.Problem Formulation.",
    "Given a vehicle camera video V ∈ R T ×H×W ×C with T frames, the event boundary sequence s = {(start i, end i)} P i=1 with P phases, and a list of pedestrian bounding boxes b= {(x st i, x ed i, y st i, y ed i)} n i=1for n < T frames, the goal is to generate two sequences ṽ = { ṽi } L v i=1 for vehicle and p = { pi } L p i=1 for pedestrian that contain both the temporal information and the textual descriptions for all P phases.",
    "The final P captions of both targets, v = {v i } P i=1 and p = {p i } P i=1, can be decoded and extracted directly from ṽ and p. For fine-tuning, the final loss is calculated by combining the losses for generating the vehicle and pedestrian output sequences.",
    "Visual Feature ExtractionMain Feature."
